{
  "texts": [
    "The use of AL was fundamental to improve the performance of the deep learning model to classify land-use following deforestation for continental Africa over the traditional model training approaches (see Fig. 1).",
    "Particularly in cases where the training data is limited, heterogeneous or is prone to labeling errors (i.e.",
    "shape correctness, a mix of land uses), the model using the original data is not able to generalize across regions.",
    "In such cases AL is shown to be required to achieve higher accuracy in the prediction process 47, 48.",
    "In our study, the only class that obtains good performance using the original data is cacao, which maintains this high accuracy on the two AL iterations (Fig. 1)."
  ]
}